  "prompt": "Is Bernie Sanders a populist?",
  "response": "Yes, Bernie Sanders is often described as a populist. Populism generally refers to political movements that claim to represent the interests and voices of the common people, often in opposition to established elites. Sanders, a U.S. Senator from Vermont, has built his political career on advocating for policies that he argues will benefit the middle and working classes. His platform includes proposals like Medicare for All, raising the minimum wage, breaking up big banks, and making public college tuition-free. These positions, along with his rhetoric that often critiques economic inequality and corporate influence in politics, align with populist themes.",
